findings.suggested_fix:
Split into two tests for clearer failure attribution. Example:

@Test
fun malformed_nonUri_blocked() {
    handler.openUri("not a uri at all")
    assertNull(shadowOf(application).nextStartedActivity)
}

@Test
fun malformed_empty_blocked() {
    handler.openUri("")
    assertNull(shadowOf(application).nextStartedActivity)
}

Keep both behind a shared @Before that clears the activity queue (already present).

Optional: add a test that uses a PackageManager-less context or Shadows.shadowOf(application).setCheckActivities(true) + no registered resolver, then calls openUri with 'http://example.com' and asserts no exception escapes. Example:

@Test
fun http_startActivity_failure_is_swallowed() {
    shadowOf(application).setCheckActivities(true) // forces ActivityNotFoundException
    // no exception expected
    handler.openUri("http://example.com")
}

Low priority — defensive branch, task TDD anchor does not require it.

Decide the policy and pin it. If case-insensitive is desired (recommended — RFC 3986 §3.1 declares schemes case-insensitive), change SafeUriHandler to: val scheme = ... .lowercase() and add a test:

@Test
fun http_allowed_uppercase_scheme() {
    handler.openUri("HTTP://example.com")
    assertNotNull(shadowOf(application).nextStartedActivity)
}

If case-sensitive is intentional, add a negative test to lock it in:

@Test
fun http_uppercase_scheme_blocked_by_design() {
    handler.openUri("HTTP://example.com")
    assertNull(shadowOf(application).nextStartedActivity)
}
